Anambra State Governor-elect, Prof. Chukwuma Soludo has arrived at Golden Tulip Hotels, Agulu Lake in Anaocha Local Government Area for the inauguration of the Transition Committee for his swearing-in in March. Soludo had sparked nationwide debate last week when he announced an 80-man list as the transition committee for his swearing-in. Soludo was welcome by the chairperson to the committee, Dr (Mrs) Oby Ezekwesili, who affectionately hugged him upon entry into the hall. Most members of the committee were already seated when the governor-elect arrived. Other members of the committee who welcomed Soludo included: Hon Ben Nwankwo, Mr Chinedu Nwoye, Dr Nelson Omenugha, the Secretary to the State Government, Prof Solo Chukwulobelu; Speaker of Anambra State House of Assembly; Rt Hon Uche Okafor; and many other dignitaries.